  "texts": [
    "This occurs when deriving the bound (52), and the assumption ∥h∥ L ∞ (R+,L q (I)) < +∞ is there to ensure the L 1 (R +) integrability of the term T 2 (t) from which follows inequality (58).",
    "However, the same integrability could be recovered as soon as ∥h(t, ⋅)∥ L q (I) satisfies the weaker control (62), with τ q from (63).",
    "In particular, inequality (52) would need to be changed intoT 2 (t) ≤ η (1 + ∥log(1 + w)∥ L q ′ (I) ∥h in ∥ L q (I)) e -(τ -τq)t,and the rest of the proof would follow easily.Remark 6.",
    "We observe from condition (63) that by choosing q = 2, we can impose the least restrictive constraints on the main parameters of our model, in order to recover the convergence of h(t, w) toward the global equilibrium h ∞ (w) through Theorem 2.",
    "Indeed, for this particular choice condition (63) reads-λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε) + σ 2 ℓ ≤ λ p (ω p + ε) 2 -σ 2 p < λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε) + σ 2ℓ, and is satisfied, for example, as soon as the leaders' influence is stronger than the individuals' one in driving the consensus dynamics."
